item.title: Future Tones
item.dc:creator: woostify
item.content:encoded:
On the 25th of June 2017 I spent a nerve-wracking 6 hours taking my Introductory
Assessment. Three days later I found out that all the hard work, stress and focus had been worth it, as I had passed and was officially an Iyengar yoga teacher.

You get by with a help from your friends

I’ve had loads of support. My husband has had to step into the bedtime breach two evenings a week, as I head out the door to teach my evening classes. He never complains, in fact, he makes a point of asking how the lesson went when
I come home and root about for a snack.

The little group of ‘guinea pigs’ that I taught during my training have stuck with me through thick and thin. They
committed wholeheartedly to being my loyal test students, and then, when I passed, insisted that the class carry on, with the difference being that they now paid me. They’ve been my students for nearly three years now, and I truly feel that we evolve together.

Grateful for the Good Bits

It’s easy to focus on the negative. But, as Mr Iyengar says: “Cultivate the positive, abjure the negative.” I’ve also had teaching successes and some really excellent good bits.
I’ve arrived on time to every lesson I’ve had to teach this year, bar one.  I’ve successfully started a new class, which now has a steady core of students.

I’ve taken a student up into headstand for the first time. I’ve seen my students progress and improve, both physically and mentally. I’ve got to the end of the class and felt the peace and stillness in the room during savasana, and been deeply grateful.

Any yoga teacher will tell you that you know when you’ve taught a good class. There’s a sense of intense satisfaction and fulfilment, shared between you and your students. You’ve worked them hard, and they’ve worked hard themselves into the bargain.

item.content:encoded:
On the 25th of June 2017 I spent a nerve-wracking 6 hours taking my Introductory
Assessment. Three days later I found out that all the hard work, stress and focus had been worth it, as I had passed and was officially an Iyengar yoga teacher.

You get by with a help from your friends

I’ve had loads of support. My husband has had to step into the bedtime breach two evenings a week, as I head out the door to teach my evening classes. He never complains, in fact, he makes a point of asking how the lesson went when
I come home and root about for a snack.

The little group of ‘guinea pigs’ that I taught during my training have stuck with me through thick and thin. They
committed wholeheartedly to being my loyal test students, and then, when I passed, insisted that the class carry on, with the difference being that they now paid me. They’ve been my students for nearly three years now, and I truly feel that we evolve together.

Grateful for the Good Bits

It’s easy to focus on the negative. But, as Mr Iyengar says: “Cultivate the positive, abjure the negative.” I’ve also had teaching successes and some really excellent good bits.
I’ve arrived on time to every lesson I’ve had to teach this year, bar one.  I’ve successfully started a new class, which now has a steady core of students.

I’ve taken a student up into headstand for the first time. I’ve seen my students progress and improve, both physically and mentally. I’ve got to the end of the class and felt the peace and stillness in the room during savasana, and been deeply grateful.

Any yoga teacher will tell you that you know when you’ve taught a good class. There’s a sense of intense satisfaction and fulfilment, shared between you and your students. You’ve worked them hard, and they’ve worked hard themselves into the bargain.

item.title: The Volume Mascara
item.dc:creator: woostify
item.content:encoded: Kevyn Aucoin The Volume Mascara emboldens timid lashes with a volumizing formula designed to create a fully fanned, gravity-defying appearance. Intense black pigments give your lashes a glossy, lacquered look that perfectly frames your peepers for a dramatic effect. Jojoba oil nourishes, hydrates and conditions to prevent clumping and fading, never making your lashes feel stiff or brittle.

item.title: MultiVitamin Power Recovery Masque
item.dc:creator: woostify
item.content:encoded: Dermalogica AGE Smart MultiVitamin Power Recovery Masque features a deeply reparative formula that targets and corrects the visible signs of premature aging. Vitamins A, C, E, F and pro-vitamin B5 firm, nourish and protect the skin from environmental aggressors, boosting collagen and cell turnover. Beta-glucan and algae extract reduce fine lines and wrinkles while licorice, comfrey and burdock root extracts soothe and brighten your complexion.

item.title: BECCA Essentials Radiance Kit
item.dc:creator: woostify
item.content:encoded: Create and customize your own amazing look with Becca Cosmetics Limited Edition BECCA Essentials: Summer Radiance Kit. Packed with a silky bronzer and a luminizing primer, this kit includes all of the must-have items needed to flaunt that coveted summer glow.

item.title: Oil-Free Camouflage Concealer
item.dc:creator: woostify
item.content:encoded: Glo Skin Beauty Oil-Free Camouflage Concealer (formerly glominerals Camouflage Oil-Free Concealer) supplies highly pigmented, oil-free coverage ideal for concealing scars, hyperpigmentation, blemishes and dark circles. Vitamin A controls sebum production to aid in healing and minimizing breakouts while vitamin E repels free radicals. The soothing formula nourishes and protects, leaving you with a healthier, more even complexion.

item.title: Shakti Face and Body Resculpting Cream
item.dc:creator: woostify
item.content:encoded: Shakti Face and Body Resculpting Cream from Tracie Martyn moisturizes, contours and firms both face and body while effectively improving the appearance of dimpled skin. Designed to create an appearance of a more defined facial structure, this nourishing lotion works perfectly as a day cream and makeup base. The use of natural black currant lipids elevates its hydrating properties to deeply moisturize the skin, while organic Bulgarian rose essential oil delivers an elegant, calming aroma.

item.title: DALLAS Thickening Spray
item.dc:creator: woostify
item.content:encoded: Flaunt bigger hair with DALLAS Thickening Spray designed by R+Co. Perfect for adding that extra volume you covet, this styling spray adds body and shine to your hair.

item.title: Concord Shadow Set
item.dc:creator: woostify
item.content:encoded: Brighten up your eyelids this holiday season with this gorgeous makeup set by Glo Skin Beauty. The Concord Shadow Set is complete with four full-size cream formulas, ranging from rich metallics to earth tones. Designed to stay put for 12 hours, it includes a built-in sharpener for priming, shading and defining the eyes.

item.title: Professional-C Serum 20%
item.dc:creator: woostify
item.content:encoded: Obagi Professional-C Serum 20% infuses your skin with L-ascorbic acid, the only form of vitamin C suitable for topical application. Designed to penetrate deep into your skin, this vitamin C serum provides effective antioxidant protection from UV damage as it brightens away hyperpigmentation and encourages the growth of collagen and elastin fibers. Hyaluronic acid binds moisture to your skin to prevent dryness.

item.title: Fruit Pigmented Ultra Lengthening Mascara
item.dc:creator: woostify
item.content:encoded: 100% Pure Fruit Pigmented Ultra Lengthening Mascara let's the fruits of your labor show with your lush, full lashes. The all-natural formula contains conditioning provitamin B5, vitamin E and oat and wheat proteins to improve and produce healthier lashes. This volumizing mascara is smudge-proof and is safe for sensitive eyes.

item.title: Phytophanère Dietary Supplement
item.dc:creator: woostify
item.content:encoded: Phyto Phytophanere Dietary Supplement features nourishing vitamins, essential fatty acids and antioxidants needed to promote beautiful and healthy hair growth, nail strength and a luminous skin tone. Powered by vitamins B, C and E and omegas 3 and 6, these beauty supplements deliver the vital nutrients your body needs to function, promoting firmer skin, fewer wrinkles and stronger hair.

item.title: Facial Recovery Oil
item.dc:creator: woostify
item.content:encoded: Eminence Organics Facial Recovery Oil naturally moisturizes while combating the early signs of aging. With a mixture of fine organic botanicals, including olive oil, sesame oil and rosemary, this potent skin oil reduces the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles while soothing sensitive skin. Use day or night for a smoother, younger-looking complexion. Soy- and nut-free.
